//Help Screen Strings Help - How to hack the Pentagon: About the author: Sources for images: You are presented with a 2D array of blank buttons. Each top-secret Pentagon file to hack is hidden in one of these buttons. When you click on a blank button, one of two things will happen:\n 1) The file image will be shown, indicating that you found the file.\n 2) Our ingenious super-special hacker-scan will occur, where the number of hidden files in the same row AND column will appear on the button now.\n The objective of the game is to find ALL the hidden files using the LEAST AMOUNT of hacker-scans as possible. As you find more files, the numbers displayed on the scanned buttons will decrease. The amount of files found and the number of hacker-scans done will update. A hacker-scan will NOT occur on a button again if there was one PREVIOUSLY on it. The hacker-scan WILL occur when you click on a previously UNCOVERED FILE. When all files are found, YOU WIN! The game will return to the main menu afterwards.\n To change the NUMBER OF FILES to find and the DIMENSIONS of the button array, go to the OPTIONS MENU on the main menu.
Jacob Wharrie is a computing science student at Simon Fraser University. He is currently taking CMPT 276.
